definition.value: Neofusicoccum parvum is a vascular pathogen that causes severe decline and dieback symptoms in grapevines worldwide.

Wheat streak mosaic virus (WSMV) is a plant pathogenic virus of the family Potyviridae that infects plants in the Poaceae family, especially wheat (Triticum spp.); it is globally distributed and vectored by the wheat curl mite, particularly in regions where wheat is widely grown.
Colletotrichum graminicola (teleomorph Glomerella graminicola) is a filamentous ascomycete that causes anthracnose disease of maize.
